s=title> *** Remedy Recruitment Information ***</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>About Remedy</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Remedy is a raid oriented EverQuest guild on the Maelin Starpyre server (we moved from The Nameless in march 2003) formed in january 2001. Our goal is to explore and conquer all of EverQuest's raid content and most importantly have fun doing that. We are currently focusing on the Planes of Power expansion. Take a look at our <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.remedyguild.com">website</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> to find out what we have been up to.<br>
<br>
Our members come from all over the world, Australia, Asia, Europe, North America. Common language in guild chat and on the message board is English. We raid at European prime time (sometimes earlier/longer on weekends):<br>
<br>
8pm-1am CET (Central European Time)<br>
2pm-7pm EST (Eastern Standard Time)<br>
11am-4pm PST (Pacific Standard Time)<br>
2am-7am TW (Taiwan time)<br>
<br>
We use a point system to award loot.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Recruitment requirements</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
We are always looking for talented players who like to work in a team, play a lot and love raiding as much as we do. Raid attendance is very important to us, you should be able to play at least 5 days a week. You have to be able to understand and express yourself in English. Your account must be PoP enabled. You must be lvl 65 and have at least your classes most important AAs.<br>
<br>
Cross server transfers are welcome, however you will have to go through the same nomination process as &quot;native&quot; players, we cannot guarantee you a guild invitation.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Classes that we are looking for</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Cleric<br>
Beastlord<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Contact information</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
If you think Remedy is the right guild for you then don't hesitate to contact us. Either leave a post on the message board or send a tell to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bayla</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Chwing</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> or <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Dage</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. Don't give up if you don't get an immediate reply, there's usually a good deal of spam during raids and tells can be easily missed or the person you send a tell to is just too busy to reply at the moment.<br>
<br>
